Definition of moral terms

    / For a general index of all terms
        : see http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/refractory/index.brec

    form F
        ─ mass noun
            - Promotion of a maximum, universal sum of personal freedom.
                : see http://reluk.ca/project/proto-waycast/moral_forms.xht#F
    form G
        ─ mass noun
            - Relation of the personal to the endmost goal of the person.
                : see http://reluk.ca/project/proto-waycast/moral_forms.xht#G
    human rights
        ─ plural noun
            : join @ `^^rights$`
                / *All* things have these rights.
    right
        ─ adjective
            - Having the forms G and F, and not thereby being wrong.
                : see http://reluk.ca/project/proto-waycast/normative_ethic.xht#ethic
        ─ count noun
            - A moral entitlement, one of *right to G* or *right to F*.
                : see http://reluk.ca/project/proto-waycast/normative_ethic.xht#rights
        ─ mass noun
            - That which is right.
                : re `right` see `^^─ adjective$` @ `^^right$`
    rightful
        ─ adjective
            - Morally entitled according to a right.
    rights
        ─ plural noun
            : see `^^─ count noun$` @ `^^right$`
    right to F
        ─ noun
            - A moral entitlement to promote a maximum, universal sum of personal freedom
              while thereby infringing no right.
                : see http://reluk.ca/project/proto-waycast/normative_ethic.xht#right_to_F
    right to G
        ─ noun
            - A moral entitlement to relate the personal to the endmost goal of the person
              while thereby infringing no right.
                : see http://reluk.ca/project/proto-waycast/normative_ethic.xht#right_to_G
    wrong
        ─ adjective
            - Countering a form G or F that is not itself wrong.
                : see http://reluk.ca/project/proto-waycast/normative_ethic.xht#ethic
        ─ noun
            - A thing which is wrong.
                : re `wrong` see `^^─ adjective$` @ `^^wrong$`
    wrongful
        ─ adjective
            : join @ `^^wrong$`


